Earth is under attack!

The Chitauri, a species from a galaxy far far away, are invading our beloved planet to make it their own.
The brain behind this attack: Loki - a galactic villain with superpowers who is trying to conquer more and more planets in the universe to expand his army.
His first target on Earth: San Francisco! He has opened a portal above the Transamerica Pyramid for the Chitauri to enter, using the Tesseract.
Humanity's only chance are the Avengers - a group of heroes with superpowers - and YOU!


You need to help the Avengers defeat Loki and the Chitauri to save Earth and humanity from extinction. Can you manage to do it?
Let's see who is on your team:

__You__:
\+ Incredible battle strategist with very low risk for misjudgment.
\- Nearly no combat skills and will require help of Avengers.

Captain America:
+ Superhuman strength and agility with unbreakable shield.
- Limited to human-level vulnerabilities.

Hulk:
+ Incredible strength and nearly invincible.
- Uncontrollable rage that can become a threat to teammates and civilians.

Thor (Brother of Loki):
+ God of Thunder, controlling lightning and his destructive hammer Mjlnir.
- His confidence leads him to underestimate enemies, and he is vulnerable to powerful magical forces.

Iron Main:
+ Powerful, versatile high-tech suit with weapons and armor.
- Heavy reliance on the suit.

Hawkeye:
+ Master marksman with deadly precision using his bow and arrow.
- Lacks superhuman abilities, making him rely solely on his weapon.

Black Widow:
+ Expert combat skills and tactical intelligence.
- Lacks superhuman abilities, leaving her vulnerable to physical attacks.

Watch the intro scene to this game here:
https://youtu.be/ffbwvnatK80

The idea for this game is based on:
Marvel Studios. (2012). The Avengers [Film]. Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures.

#Defining win and fail function
def win():
    print('*' * 100)
    #Art for win
    art = """
           A      M       M      A    ZZZZZZ   III  N    N   GGGGG
          A A     MM     MM     A A       Z     I   NN   N  G     G
         A   A    M M   M M    A   A     Z      I   N N  N  G      
         AAAAA    M  M M  M    AAAAA    Z       I   N  N N  G   GGG
         A   A    M   M   M    A   A   Z        I   N   NN  G     G
         A   A    M       M    A   A  Z         I   N    N  G     G
         A   A    M       M    A   A  ZZZZZZ   III  N    N   GGGGG
"""
    print(art)
    print('*' * 100)
    #Win statement
    print("""\n!!! Congratulations !!! 
You and the Avengers have successfully defeated Loki and the Chitauri!
Thank you fighting for San Francisco and Earth!\n
WE ARE SAVED!\n""")
    #calling restart function if user wants to play again
    restart()

def fail():
    #separation from text
    print('-' * 100)
    #Fail statement
    print("""\nThe Avengers are overrun. San Francisco has fallen. 
Loki and the Chitauri will take over our planet...\n""")
    #calling restart function to try again
    restart()

#Defining restart function
def restart():
    restart_question = input(prompt = "Do you want to restart the game? (Yes/No)\n>> ").casefold()
    if 'y' in restart_question or 'yes' in restart_question:
        print()
        #calling game_launch if user wants to restart
        game_launch()
    elif 'n' in restart_question or 'no' in restart_question:
        #calling game_end function if user does not want to restart
        game_end()
    else:
        print("\nInvalid input! Try again.")
        #goes back to question if invalid input
        restart()

#Defining game end function
def game_end():
    print("\nThank you for playing!")
    

    
#Defining game launch
def game_launch():    
    #Gives player a name to use during the game.
    print('-' * 100)
   
    #Welcome text for user
    print(f"\nThank you for fighting for Earth and helping the Avengers!\n")
    print("You better get started, you are running out of time!" )
    input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
    #Calling stage_1 to begin the game
    stage_1()


#Defining first stage of the game
def stage_1():
    #Stage explanation
    print("""The Avengers gather in a circle, standing back-to-back, on the intersection of Columbus Ave and Broadway,
looking up to the Transamerica Pyramid in disbelief. Hundreds of Chitauri are rushing through Loki's portal. 
They are approaching the Avengers aggressively and start firing laser weapons from their spaceships.
The Avengers need to defend this attack wave!\nNow it is up to you to decide who to send into this battle!\n""")

    
#List of Avengers not including player's hero name
    avengers = ["captain america",
        "hulk", 
        "thor",
        "iron man",
        "hawkeye",
        "black widow"]

#Give player choices of who to send into the fight.
    print("Who are you sending into the fight?\n")
    for avenger in avengers:
        print(avenger.title())
    stage_1_choice()

#Choice conditionals
def stage_1_choice():
    #User input
    avenger_choice = input(prompt = "\nChoose an Avenger!\n>> ").casefold()
    
    #Captain America conditional - support1
    if 'captain america' in avenger_choice:
        print("\n--> Captain America can't fight them all. He needs support from another Avenger!")
        #Calling support_1() to continue 
        support_1()
    
    #Hulk conditional - win
    elif 'hulk' in avenger_choice:
        print("""\n--> The laser weapons of the Chitauri can't do much damage to the Hulk!
He manages to fight the whole wave of Chitauri and crunches their spaceships. Excellent choice!\n""")
        # Calling stage 2 to continue the game
        stage_2()
      
    #Thor conditional - win
    elif 'thor' in avenger_choice:
        print("\n--> Thor calls the lightning! All ships collapse from overvoltage! Good thinking!\n")
        # Calling stage 2 to continue the game
        stage_2()
        
    #Iron Man conditional - win
    elif 'iron man' in avenger_choice:
        print("""\n--> The Iron Man uses his high-tech weapons to smash the Chitauri's spaceships! Good Thinking!\n""")
            # Calling stage 2 to continue the game
        stage_2()
    
    #Hawkeye conditional - support 2
    elif 'hawkeye' in avenger_choice:
        print("""\n--> Hawkeye can't fire his bow fast enough to deal with the amount of Chitauri. 
He is calling for support!""")
        #Calling support_2 to continue stage 1
        support_2()
        
    #Black Widow conditional - fail
    elif 'black widow' in avenger_choice:
        print("\n--> Black Widow can only do ground combat. She can't do much in this fight against the spaceships.")
        #Calling fail function
        input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
        fail()
    #Invalid input returns user to input choice again    
    else:
        #For invalid input
        print("\n// Invalid input. Please choose an Avenger from the list.")
        stage_1_choice()
        
        
#Defining support_1 if Captain America is chosen
def support_1():
    avenger_support_1 = input(prompt = """Who are you sending to support Captain America? (Choose another Avenger)
Hint: Consider strengths and weaknesses of the Avengers.\n>> """).casefold()
    
    #Hulk conditional - win
    if 'hulk' in avenger_support_1:
        print("""\n--> The laser weapons of the Chitauri can't do much damage to the Hulk! 
He manages to fight the whole wave of Chitauri and crunches their spaceships. Excellent choice!\n""")
        # Calling stage 2 to continue the game
        stage_2()
    
    #Hawkeye conditional - win
    elif 'hawkeye' in avenger_support_1:
        print("""\n--> These two make a good team! They were able to defend this wave of Chitauri!\n""")
        # Calling stage 2 to continue the game
        stage_2()
    
    #Iron Man conditional - win
    elif 'iron man' in avenger_support_1:
        print("\n--> The Iron Man uses his high-tech weapons to destroy all Chitauri! Great Job!\n")
        # Calling stage 2 to continue the game
        stage_2()
    
    #Thor conditional - win
    elif 'thor' in avenger_support_1:
        print("\n--> Thor calls the lightning! All ships collapse from overvoltage! Good thinking!\n")
        stage_2()
    
    #Black Widow conditional - fail
    elif 'black widow' in avenger_support_1:
        print("\n--> Black Widow is only able to do ground combat. She can't do much in this fight against the spaceships.")
        # Calling fail function
        input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
        fail()
    
    #If Captain America is selected again
    elif 'captain america' in avenger_support_1:
        #Return user to input support_1 again
        print("\n// You already chose this Avenger. Try again.\n")
        support_1()
        
    else:
        #Return user to input support_1 again
        print("\n// This input is not valid. Try again.")
        support_1()

#Stage 2 game development
def stage_2():    
    input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
    
    #Celebration text for winning first stage
    print("""!!! Congratulations !!! 
You have successfully repelled the attack wave of the Chitauri! But you need to keep going before 
another wave of Chitauri strikes! \n""")
    input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
    
    print('-' * 100) #stage division, introducing new scene
    print() #blank space
    
    #Stage explanation
    print("""Loki is still keeping the portal open using the Tesseract. You need to get possession of it
in order to close it. This will stop new Chitauri from entering. Thor takes up to this endeavor.
He, as Loki's brother, should be able to talk sense into him, right?\n""")
    
    time.sleep(3) #for easier readability
    
    #Game explanation for user
    print("""He makes his way to the Transamerica Pyramid, where Loki keeps the Tesseract.
Dark clouds are gathering around the portal, gusts of wind make the Transamerica Pyramid sway.
Thor approaches Loki on the top of the building to convince him to give up the Tesseract.
They have an emotional conversation involving their childhood, talking about everything they have been through
together. Loki remembers how Thor and he always used to play "Rock, Paper, Scissors" when they were little. 
He challenges Thor to play one final round for the Tesseract. Thor agrees!\n""")

    time.sleep(3) #for easier readability
    
    print("""The rule: Whoever wins 2 rounds claims victory.
The stake: The loser will leave the Tesseract to the winner!\n
\nYour task is to help Thor make his choices to win the game!\nGood Luck!\n""")
    
    #Game launch
    input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to start the game! >\n").casefold()
    
    #Creating list of game items
    rps_lst = ['rock', 'paper', 'scissors']
    
    #User wins and loki wins to track for "Best-of-3" mode
    user_wins = 0
    loki_wins = 0
    
    #While loop for "best-of-3" mode:
    while user_wins < 2 and loki_wins < 2:
    
        #Creating user input
        user_guess = input(prompt = "Pick Rock, Paper, or Scissors!\n>> ").casefold()
        print() #blank for better readability
        
        #Creating random guess for Loki
        loki_guess = random.choice(rps_lst).casefold()
        
        #When user input invalid
        if user_guess not in rps_lst:
            print("// Invalid input! Try again.")
            continue
   
        #Game logic
        else:
            print("Loki's choice: ", end = '')
            time.sleep(1.5)
            print(loki_guess.capitalize())
            time.sleep(1)
            
            #Same guess conditional
            if user_guess == loki_guess:
                print("That's a tie! Go again.\n")
            
            #User wins conditionals
            elif (user_guess == 'rock' and loki_guess == 'scissors')  or \
                 (user_guess == 'paper' and loki_guess == 'rock')     or \
                 (user_guess == 'scissors'and loki_guess == 'paper'):
                print("You win!\n")
                user_wins += 1 #User scores +1 win
            
            #Loki wins conditional
            else:
                print("You lose!\n")
                loki_wins +=1 #Loki scores +1 win
                
        #Print score after every round
        time.sleep(1)
        print(f"""The score is:
Thor: {user_wins}
Loki: {loki_wins}""")
                
        #Conditional for game result
        #User win conditional
        if user_wins == 2:
            print("""\n!!! Congratulations !!! 
You and Thor beat Loki and are now in possession of the Tesseract!\n""")
            
            #Calling stage_3 to continue game
            stage_3_launch()
        
        #Loki win conditional
        elif loki_wins == 2:
            print("\nYou lost to Loki... the Tesseract stays with Loki and you cannot close the portal.\n")
            input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
            #insert fail function
            fail()
            
        else:
            pass

#Stage_3 launch            
def stage_3_launch():
    input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
    #calling stage 3 after input
    stage_3()

#Stage_3    
def stage_3():
    print('-' * 100) #stage division, introducing new scene
    print() #blank space
    
    #Recap stage 2 win
    print("""Thor rushes to the Tesseract and closes the portal! The Chitauri can no longer enter Earth!\n""")
    
    #Stage explanation
    print("""But there are still many Chitauri that have already entered and they are about to start a new attack.
Chitauri are dependent on the Mothership. It controls all Chitauri and gives them commands. If the Mothership
is destroyed, all Chitauri will immediately stop functioning. 
This is the final step to defeat Loki and the Chitauri once and for all.\n""")

    time.sleep(3) #for easier readability
    
    #Game explanation
    print("""The Mothership has a strong electromagnetic shield for its defense. Think carefully which attacks can hurt 
it and which ones are useless!\n""")
    
    time.sleep(3) #for easier readability
    
    #Calling stage 3 choice
    stage_3_choice_1()
    
    
#Defining stage 3 user choices to reference else-conditional
def stage_3_choice_1():
    
    #Step 1 - "Destroying the Mothership"
    print("What action are you advising the Avengers to do first in order to destroy the Mothership?\n")
    
    #User choice for first part of the stage
    aveng_attack_1 = ["1. Call Hulk to use his rage to perform a critical hit on the Mothership.",
               "2. Call Thor to use lightning to disable the Mothership's electromagnetic shield.",
               "3. Call Iron Man to shoot his plasma weapons at the Mothership."]
   
    #print choices
    for attack in aveng_attack_1:
        print(attack)
    
    #try/except function if user doesn't input 1, 2, or 3
    try:
        attack_choice = input(prompt = "\nPlease input the number 1, 2, or 3.\n>> ").casefold()
        if attack_choice not in ['1', '2', '3']:
            raise ValueError("\n// Invalid input! You must input 1, 2, or 3.\n")
    except ValueError as ve:
        print(ve)
        return stage_3_choice_1() #return to input
    
    #User choice conditionals - Hulk - support1
    if attack_choice == '1':
        print("""\n--> Even Hulk's rage can't do any damage to the Mothership's strong shield.\n
You have one more chance before the Chitauri overrun the Avengers.\n""")
        attack_1_support_1() #calling support_1
    
    #Thor conditional - win
    elif attack_choice == '2':
        print("""\n--> Excellent! The incredibly high voltage of the lightning disables the Mothership's
electromagnetic shield temporarily! Now is the chance to perform the last punch. 
Hurry up, before the shield recovers!\n""")
        input(prompt = "< Press ENTER to continue! >\n").casefold()
        stage_3_choice_2_launch() #calling next part of stage - attack_2
    
    #Iron Man conditional - support2
    elif attack_choice == '3':
        print("""\n--> The Mothership's shield is too strong. Iron Man's plasma attack can't damage the shield.
You have one more chance before the Chitauri overrun the Avengers.\n""")
        attack_1_support_2() #calling support_2
    
    else:
        pass
